  "doc_id": "44700",
  "text": "In addition to microbial symbioses, many multicellular eukaryotes engage in symbioses with other multicellular organisms. Central features of these interactions are the physical linkages between constituent partners which provide an opportunity for microbial transfer, adding a layer of complexity to the factors that affect the diversity and function of individual microbiomes. Many macroscopic symbioses involve diverse partners, occur across distinct habitats, and have evolved independently multiple times across the tree of life [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] . Consequently, macroscopic symbioses provide an important framework for exploring the processes that may lead distantly related taxa to converge on microbiomes with similar genetic and functional profiles.",
